OL,3,CUnstable council finances in need of
OL,4,Cswift reform, spending watchdog warns
OL,6,FSir Geoffrey Clifton-Brown, chair of
OL,7,Fthe Commons Public Accounts Committee
OL,8,Fsaid short-term financial support
OL,9,Foffered to councils was "a sticking
OL,10,Fplaster to the underlying pressures
OL,11,Ffacing local authorities".
OL,13,FHe added: "Delays in local audits are
OL,14,Ffurther undermining public confidence
OL,15,Fin local government finances.
OL,17,F"There needs to be a cross-Government
OL,18,Fapproach to local government finance
OL,19,Freform, which must deliver effective
OL,20,Faccountability and value for money for
OL,21,Ftaxpayers."
