OL,6,FRepresentatives from local councils
OL,7,Falso urged ministers to come forward
OL,8,Fwith plans to reform the funding
OL,9,Fauthorities receive.
OL,11,FPete Marland, chair of the Local
OL,12,FGovernment Association's economy and
OL,13,Fresources board, said: "Without
OL,14,Fadequate funding, councils will
OL,15,Fcontinue to struggle to provide
OL,16,Fcrucial services ` with devastating
OL,17,Fconsequences for those who rely on
OL,18,Fthem ` and it will be impossible for
OL,19,Fthem to help the Government achieve
OL,20,Fits reform and growth agenda.
